    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single deficient factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is offset by the quantitative output comparison results (all E/uval values well below 1.96 threshold) and the strong equivalency of model inputs to physical test configuration. The overall credibility evidence package is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level conclusion for the intended regulatory use. Assessment team accepts the FEA modeling framework as credible for predicting ASTM F1717 compression-bending behavior of the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
